quran[16]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,109,""
  37,110,"Thus indeed do We reward the Muhsinûn (good-doers - See V.2:112)."
  37,111,"Verily, he was one of Our believing slaves."
  38,88,""
  39,73,"And those who kept their duty to their Lord (Al-Muttaqûn{1}) will be led to Paradise in groups, till, when they reach it, and its gates will be opened (before their arrival for their reception) and its keepers will say: Salâmun ‘Alaikum (peace be upon you)! You have done well, so enter here to abide therein.",footnotes:1:(V.73) "Al-Muttaqûn" See (V.2:2).
  39,74,"And they will say: "
  39,75,"And you will see the angels surrounding the Throne (of Allâh) from all round, glorifying the praises of their Lord (Allâh). And they (all the creatures) will be judged with truth. And it will be said, "
  40,52,"The Day when their excuses will be of no profit to Zâlimûn (polytheists, wrong-doers and disbelievers in the Oneness of Allâh). Theirs will be the curse, and theirs will be the evil abode (i.e. painful torment in Hell-fire)."
  40,53,"And, indeed We gave Mûsâ (Moses) the guidance, and We caused the Children of Israel to inherit the Scripture [i.e. the Taurât (Torah)] -"
  40,54,"A guide and a reminder for men of understanding."
  41,31,""
  41,32,""
  41,33,"And who is better in speech than he who [says: "
  42,16,"And those who dispute concerning Allâh (His religion of Islâmic Monotheism with which Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم has been sent), after it has been accepted (by the people), of no use is their dispute before their Lord and on them is wrath, and for them will be a severe torment.{1}",footnotes:1:(V.16) See the footnote of (Verse 3:85).
  42,17,"It is Allâh Who has sent down the Book (the Qur’ân) in truth, and the Balance (i.e. to act justly). And what can make you know that perhaps the Hour is close at hand?"
  42,18,"Those who believe not therein seek to hasten it, while those who believe are fearful of it, and know that it is the very truth. Verily, those who dispute concerning the Hour are certainly in error far away."